The kalemne problem is just that she was wotc’s chance to make a good RW commander that wasn’t combat-oriented. Instead they made a bad RW Commander that was combat-oriented. And Ezuri is the reason. They gave him territory that should have been hers. 

Look at Alesha. Or Mentor of the Meek. Or Grenzo. The colors that care about small creatures are red and white. Ezuri is the exact opposite of that. It’s a color pie break. Even blue doesn’t care about small creatures, it just has them. Ezuri is green, which ramps and casts big creatures. It makes more sense for Ezuri to have the experience trigger for big creatures and kalemne to have a trigger for small ones. 

Ask any Ezuri player and they’ll probably tell you how tough it is to get experience with him. It’s possible but you jump through hoops. Meren, daxos, and mizzix, it comes naturally, but Ezuri it’s weird. The best Ezuri enablers are in fact avenger of zendikar, mycoloth, and hornet queen, which are all five mana or higher creatures that would trigger kalemne. 

Long nerdy rant that jason will make fun of me for caring too much, but it was damn disappointing that wotc made a shit commander because they can’t stop giving the stuff those underrepresented colors should get and giving them to other colors. Red and white suck in commander because wotc can’t stop fawning over green and blue instead. The kalemne problem.
